article.headline: Middle Tenn. St. 81, TENN Wesleyan 46
article.story: MURFREESBORO, Tenn. (AP) -- Marcus Morrison scored 15 points to lead Middle Tennessee State to an 81-46 victory Thursday over cold-shooting Tennessee Wesleyan. Middle Tennessee (3-2) jumped out to a 34-19 halftime lead and coasted as the Bulldogs (2-7) shot only 31.1 percent for the game, including just 6-of-25 3-pointers. Kyle Young added 12 points for Middle Tennessee, Michael Cuffee had 11 and Fats Cuyler 10. Cuffee also had a game-high 14 rebounds. The Blue Raiders shot 45.2 percent for the game, and controlled the boards 54-33. Mark Riden scored 13 points for the Bulldogs and was their only player in double figures.
